      "source": [
        "\"\"\"Comparing Models\n",
        "Two object detection models (Model A and Model B) have the following results:\n",
        "Model A:\n",
        "•\tTP = 120, TN = 150, FP = 30, FN = 20\n",
        "Model B:\n",
        "•\tTP = 140, TN = 130, FP = 40, FN = 10\n",
        "1.\tCalculate precision, recall, and F1-score for both models.\n",
        "2.\tWhich model performs better in terms of:\n",
        "o\tPrecision?\n",
        "o\tRecall?\n",
        "o\tF1-score?\n",
        "\"\"\"\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5z2nTG8rnMlg"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "#Calculation of precision\n",
        "''' Precision= TP/(TP+FP)\n",
        "Recall = TP/(TP+FN)\n",
        "F1=2*(Precision*Recall)/Precision+recall'''"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qXU7y8xxnaBu"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "model_values={\n",
        "    'A':{'TP':120, 'TN': 150, 'FP' : 30, 'FN': 20},\n",
        "    'B': {'TP' : 140, 'TN' : 130, 'FP' : 40, 'FN' : 10}\n",
        "}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "w0u9mJGzn2tI"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def metrics_calculation(x):\n",
        "  Precision= x['TP']/(x['TP']+x['FP'])\n",
        "  Recall =x['TP']/(x['TP']+x['FN'])\n",
        "  F1=2*(Precision*Recall)/(Precision+Recall)\n",
        "  return Precision, Recall, F1"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kjzPTJ_ioZ1T"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "for i,j in model_values.items():\n",
        "    p,r,f1=metrics_calculation(j)\n",
        "    print(f\"Model Name{i}: Precision: {round(p,2)}, Recall: {round(r,2)}, F1-Score: {round(f1,2)}\")"
